<subSubSection id="D77B413142CFFD961B56269E8912397E" pageId="0" pageNumber="119" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="3604476AE6AF99A75E456D6D4B29AEFC" pageId="0" pageNumber="119">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4768E046F19ABB1B64AC4EE1975CD910" pageId="0" pageNumber="119">
<taxonomicName id="D5171C19456D3648B33737249BD930BA" authorityName="Chen &amp; Li" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Aphelinidae" genus="Coccophagus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Coccophagus breviclavulus" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="breviclavulus">
<emphasis id="7917BC49F0F2D80CB215B22218B8A147" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="119">Coccophagus breviclavulus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. can be distinguished from females of other species in this genus by the following combination of characters: scape largely white, and with two broad and short dark streaks distally (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="142828D63A1CC799384FF7EB533E4C5B" captionStart="Figures 1–8" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 8. Coccophagus anchoroides 1 body, dorsal view 2 head 3 antenna, inset shows the colour of outer surface of scape 4 mesosoma 5 fore wing 6 hind wing 7 mid leg 8 metasoma." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1091.80065.figures1-8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/666979" pageId="0" pageNumber="119">3</figureCitation>
); F2 and F3 white; mesosoma (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="44286BEC39AAB9E14980068424FDCD72" captionStart="Figures 9–16" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 9 - 16. Coccophagus breviclavulus sp. nov. 9 body, dorsal view 10 head 11 antenna 12 mesosoma 13 fore wing 14 hind wing 15 legs, from left to right: fore-, mid- and hind-leg 16 metasoma." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1091.80065.figures9-16" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/666980" pageId="0" pageNumber="119">12</figureCitation>
) most brown, with two longitudinal yellow lines medially on mid lobe of mesoscutum; metasoma largely dark brown as in Figs 
<figureCitation id="515DD3AB9BA212808393FE080ADE3194" captionStart="Figures 9–16" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 9 - 16. Coccophagus breviclavulus sp. nov. 9 body, dorsal view 10 head 11 antenna 12 mesosoma 13 fore wing 14 hind wing 15 legs, from left to right: fore-, mid- and hind-leg 16 metasoma." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1091.80065.figures9-16" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/666980" pageId="0" pageNumber="119">9</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="A24E30E7B042E885ACEB3B59FB26A191" captionStart="Figures 9–16" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figures 9 - 16. Coccophagus breviclavulus sp. nov. 9 body, dorsal view 10 head 11 antenna 12 mesosoma 13 fore wing 14 hind wing 15 legs, from left to right: fore-, mid- and hind-leg 16 metasoma." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1091.80065.figures9-16" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/666980" pageId="0" pageNumber="119">16</figureCitation>
; 
<figureCitation id="E059FA8F0D0A5A17A6788C3096210ABD" captionStart="Figures 1–8" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 8. Coccophagus anchoroides 1 body, dorsal view 2 head 3 antenna, inset shows the colour of outer surface of scape 4 mesosoma 5 fore wing 6 hind wing 7 mid leg 8 metasoma." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1091.80065.figures1-8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/666979" pageId="0" pageNumber="119">F1</figureCitation>
- 
<figureCitation id="DE1CFB89B62089D9C259893B2AD0443A" captionStart="Figures 17–24" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figures 17 - 24. Coccophagus perlucidus sp. nov. 17 body, dorsal view 18 head 19 antenna 20 mesosoma 21 fore wing 22 hind wing 23 legs, from left to right: fore-, mid- and hind-leg 24 metasoma." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1091.80065.figures17-24" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/666981" pageId="0" pageNumber="119">F3</figureCitation>
with the same length; clavomeres obviously wider than funicle segments.
</paragraph>
<caption id="9025F830082EB291C081ECE0A22BC291" doi="10.3897/zookeys.1091.80065.figures9-16" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/666980" pageId="0" pageNumber="119" start="Figures 9–16" startId="F2">
